    <section id="id11546915">
      <title>Exercises</title>
<exercise id="fs-id5372394">
  <problem id="fs-id15032742">
    <list id="fs-id15456046" list-type="enumerated"><title>Evaluate the following items using increment or decrement:</title><item>True or false: <code>x = x - 1;</code> and <code>x -= 1;</code> and <preformat display="inline"><code>x--;</code></preformat> and <preformat display="inline"><code>--x;</code></preformat> all accomplish decrement.</item>
	<item>Given: <code>int y = 26;</code> and <code>int z;</code> what values will y and z have after: <code>z = y++;</code></item>
	<item>Given: <code>double x = 4.44;</code> and <code>int y;</code> what values will x and y have after: <preformat display="inline"><code>y = --x;</code></preformat></item>
	<item>As an expression: <code>10 / ++(money * 4)</code> Is this ok? Why or why not?</item>
</list>
  </problem>
  <solution id="fs-id3946633">
    <list id="fs-id15455157" list-type="enumerated"><title>Answers:</title><item>true</item>
	<item>y is: 27 and z is: 26</item>
	<item>x is: 3.44 and y is: 3   Note: truncation of 3.44 to 3 upon demotion to integer data type.</item>
	<item> Not ok. Error, the item incremented must have Lvalue attributes, usually a variable. Because of the parentheses, it is an expression not a variable.</item>
</list>
  </solution>
</exercise>
